commit_message:
Add packs and discovery queries to osquery config

The OsqueryProbes are groups by discovery configuration in packs. Probes
without discovery queries are kept in the schedule section of the

Fix monolith enrollment packages

The previous commit ce338c7fd8c introduced a bug. It is not possible to
build the enrollment package when they are downloaded if they are
missing. Their checksum would be different than the one present in the
pkg_info when the catalog was built, and munki would reject them. (The
checksum is updated by build_manifest_enrollment_package, but it is too
late.)

The rebuild_manifest_enrollment_packages command should be used instead,
if some packages are missing.

We also fix a bug in the osquery enrollment package. When we added the
option to disable or enable the file carver, we forgot the previously
configured osquery enrollment packages which didn't have the option. We
set it to "disabled" per default, like in the enrollment package form.

Add printer management via munki/monolith

Upload PPDs. Add printers to business unit manifests. The printers will
be installed / uninstalled using "nopkg" Pkginfo. The scripts are
automatically generated from the information collected in the form. The
PPDs are downloaded from monolith by the "postinstall" script. If
drivers need to be installed, the package containing them can be marked
as "required" by the printer.
Credit Graham Gilbert for printer-pkginfo

Better password validation and session management

Django password validators can be used now with the
AUTH_PASSWORD_VALIDATORS variable in base.json

Password history is saved.

MAX_PASSWORD_AGE_DAYS can be used in the django section of base.json to
force a password change after a certain number of days.

accounts.password_validation.PasswordNotAlreadyUsedValidator can be used
as password validator to check that the passwords are unique per user.

The SESSION_COOKIE_AGE and SESSION_EXPIRE_AT_BROWSER_CLOSE variables are
copied from the django section of base.json into the django settings, if
present. This enables a better control of the session validity.

munki nopkg install check script mandatory

The install check script in a munki nopkg pkginfo is mandatory. If
absent, the script will be considered installed, and the postinstall
script will never be executed.

A default install check script is provided, but it should be edited to
avoid triggering the postinstall script at each Munki run.

commit_message:
Fix connection close issues for APNS

Implement a retry logic to deal with closed connection errors.

Fix product archive title bug

get_product_archive_title() was used to find out if a package was a
product archive. Not anymore.

A package is a product archive if it is based on a product archive, or
if extra packages are provided. If a package is a product archive, we
use the get_product_archive_title() method to get its title.

commit_message:
Fix workers and queues

Add process and store queues bindings migration
Add probe pk in serialized incident
Add incident severity to probe updates
Add max_incident_severity to MetaMachine
Register incidents events
Add inventory drilldown incident severity filter
Rearrange the drill down filters

Add incidents views.

Move the machine macos apps to a separate view.
Add the machine incidents to the machine view.
Move the machine heartbeats to the top.
Remove duplicated links objects in drilldown

max machine incident severity labels

Also: moved the inventory templates into the inventory app.
Add incidents events page
Not severity label if severity is None
Fix incident events elasticsearch query
Update machine incident status
Incidents links in machine events
Add machine incident updated_at
Update incident status
Disable incident update link if not possible
Fix xlsx export with lazy gettext strings

Add Azure AD info to inventory

info from osquery queries and updated jamf api client
Move groups after links in ms display

Fix incident search form

Remove duplicated statuses and severities
Add GeoIP info

Update elacticsearch store for version >= 7

Index mapping, document _type detection, …

Move queue migration in worker getter.

Avoid migration at every app start
Fix dependencies on urllib3
Add home dir for zentral in docker container

distribute_tls_server_certs config option

Distribute the tls server certs and configure the clients to use them
only if this is set to True (default == True).

Add celery worker

Refactor osquery file carving session pre processor into a celery task.
Refactor the MDM preprocessing as celery tasks.
Run the preprocessors in one preprocess worker, consuming from queues
connected to one raw_events exchange.
Use routing keys to target different queues for the raw_events.
Move the inventory XLSX export to a background celery task.
API views for machine exports, task results

Better santa enrollment

Move the machine ID to a plist
Do not store enrollment script, config profile and plist
Start the filebeat app
Add inventory zip csv export
Add max incident severity to machine exports

First filebeat enrollment package.

Ship the santa logs
Use santa log timestamp for event created_at
Add filebeat ip address to santa log events
Filebeat cfg forms + xnumon contrib app

Remove audit contrib app

We have xnumon now.
Add a S/N cache in xnumon preprocessor
Use cache for ip lookup in enrich phase
Use cache to serialize machine info in events

query for machine type, platform, mbu & tag ids

First step to speed up the event probe filtering
Use the new method to filter the probes

Move kombu migrations to extra_context

This way, the migrations happen after a connection is established and
before everything starts.

Enrich jamf computer policy finished events

Query the API for the jamf policy general information, and add it to the
event.
Fix jamf webhooks for v10.12

Fix jamf policy event elastic indexing error

TODO: better than that!

Fix filebeat release download bug

Avoid the compression type guessing in the tarfile library. tarfile will
do a seek operation if one read operation fails, and seek operations are
not great on file like urllib3 response objects.

Pick correct santa version for enrollment pkg

The notarized and not-notorized versions have the same filename.
Add and use S/N in the filebeat client certs
Verify S/N if present in CSR via SCEP
Fix push certificate loading
Remove special subdomain for client cert auth
Fix mdm scep verification view
Fix download DEPToken public key view
Better filebeat inputs + jamf filbeat cfg
Update logstash config for filebeat contrib app
Different event classes for xnumon eventcode

Add XnumonImageExecEvent aggregations

Also, option to sort results in table aggregation
Xnumon image signature "undefined" per default
make filebeat crt and key paths more flexible
Fix events preprocessors
Kibana index pattern config for the links

Add filebeat enrollment linux script

Better scepclient and filebeat releases management
certificate_authority parameter for enrollments

Better error handling if payload signature error

Default to no signature
Log the openssl error message
Remove unsupported jamf logs

index.mapping.total_fields.limit => 2000

Added parameter in base.json too.
Remove lru_cache for geoloc

Remove lru_cache from filebeat secret => s/n

Have to build it in a better way.

Fix santa and jamf preprocessors filebeat dep.

Only try to start the santa log and jamf beat preprocessors if the
filebeat app is configured.
Add xnumon stats event

Split domains for client cert authentication

There are a lot of problems with the optional client certificate
authentication on a single domain. As soon as a valid client cert for
the domain in present in the keychain (MDM for example), it will be used
by santa, or safari.
With this commit, we undo the recent work, but we try to keep only one
certificate, using the Subject Alternative Name extension. This way,
only one chain has to be distributed to the clients.

Fix docker build for python buster based images

libssl1.0-dev necessary to build the xar tools is now installed from the
stretch (old-stable) repository.

Better fix for xar compilation on debian buster

HACK: Change the openssl library detection in the xar autoconf.
Do not mix stretch packages with buster packages.
Use yaml.SafeLoader for config files

Cache MetaMachine inv filtering values

This should speed up the events probes filtering
Add iPadOS, tvOS platforms and TV type
Export incidents prometheus metrics
Max incident severity export
Add export_inventory_to_es command
Add bundles to export_inventory_to_es

Jamf instance info → observer event metadata

The jamf instance info were part of the event payload. Because the
elasticsearch event store uses the event type as a namespace for the
event attributes, the jamf instance info could not be simply extracted
when working with more than one type of event.
By moving the jamf instance info into a metadata attribute, we make sure
that they are not namespaced by the elasticsearch store.
We use the ECS observer fields.
Display observer and request.geo in events

Add first two inventory exporters

* machine snapshot exporter to ES
* aggregations exporter to ES
Add request geo repr to distributed query tables
Fix santa log preprocess error on log rotation
Ship jamf client logs
Add Okta event hook contrib app
Fix tls host for cli cert auth for linux/filebeat
Fix osquery releases

Filter out osquery prereleases, drafts, …

Also releases w/o assets

Add azure log analytics store

Common store error handling too
Better message error handling
Fix santa log parsing
Restart the workers when they fail
Cleanup inventory AzureADInfo orphans
Fix cache use with bad serial numbers
Add powershell osquery enrollment script
Rename post_jamf_event function

Fix filebeat models

EnrolledMachine serial number is unique

Fix the jamf beat preprocessor

Fix the jamf instance lookup
Use the event metadata observer

Better filebeat event utils

Make sure that it works for external client certs
Use the EnrolledMachine to find the serial number

Fix the santa log parsing tests

Remove the filebeat contrib app dependency
Fix link, direct to current release informations
fix

Fix the ES deprecation warn on date aggregations

see https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/7.3/search-aggregations-bucket-datehistogram-aggregation.html
Kibana itself is causing the remaining warnings.
Add operator (IN / NOT IN) to payload filters

Allow multiple payload filter item on same attr

Also fix the issues with SantaProbe and MunkiInstallProbe
Better? scripts and packages download buttons

Better osquery release management

Download the assets from Github now, with a fallback for older osquery
versions.

Event store error handling in probe events

empty response is better displayed
error from the store is logged and a message is displayed
Better elasticsearch boolean payload filtering

Payload matching on str(value)

Fix matching issues with integers and booleans
Incident event store links

Fix munki install probe matching

This now works with ES and in the probe matching

Fix TimeGenerated in azure log analytics store

Conversion to UTC
Always remove the TZ
Better millisecond rounding
Fix datetime conversion issue on python < 3.6
Better incident serialization in events

commit_message:
Machine PrincipalUser and Certificates

* Remove AzureADInfo
* Get some device certificates and company portal user info with osquery and
munki postflight
Fix machine snapshot sources display and ordering

Remove gist export

Has been needing oauth for a while now.

Fix jamf webhooks missing value indexing error

Remove some empty values from jamf webhook events.

Add ON DELETE CASCADE on ms certificates m2m model

We need to be able to automatically drop the m2m tuples linking machine
snapshots to other inventory models for the cleanup_inventory_history
management command to work.

Use elasticsearch-py recovery method

The "feature" attribute of the get method of indices doesn't exist
anymore.

Fixes #93

Fix santa package extraction

Remove stapled notarization ticket from DMG file before passing it to
7z.
Fix #97.

Introduce the Realms

First thing working: refactoring of the SAML login using realms with the
saml backend.
Refactor realm claim mappings

Add OpenID Connect realm backend

Not functional yet.

OpenID connect realms start working

Tested with the login
Add LDAP realms backend
OTA enrollment with realm authentication
DEP virtual srv dev sync in the GUI and API
Webview for DEP realm authentication
Avoid divide by 0

AwaitingConfiguration + AccountConfiguration

Use the DEP realm auth to send an AccountConfiguration command during
the AwaitingConfiguration window.

BUG: the auto admin account password does not work. Problem with the
password hash
Fix AccountConfiguration hash issue
Remote users cannot view or edit realms settings
Do not include scepclient binary in docker build
convert accounts urls to paths
Add santa EnableBadSignatureProtection cfg param
Add func to get macos version from build number

Move password hash module

Remove unused slack logger. Fix import error during tests.
Fix es inventory aggregation

Upgrade bootstrap to v3.3.7

Add compatibility with jquery >= 3

Upgrade jquery to v3.5.1

Fix CSP inline script policy error
Add CSP middleware
Mark session cookie secure
No CSP header in debug views

Better openidc realm backend

* ID token verification
* Use /userinfo endpoint if available to enrich the claims

Better LDAP realm form

Check bind
Carry password forward
Hide some realm config attribute values
Hide openidc realm client secret in form
Fix realm display

Disable form CSP rule

see https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy/form-action
Form redirects blocked in some browsers, and form redirects are needed
for the OIDC and SAML realms.
Need more work: would need to get the redirect domains from the realms configuration,
and cache them.
Avoid serialization error with RealmUser
add splunk event store
Create FUNDING.yml
Add options for google cloud storage
Postgres host and pwd override from base.json
Fix celery and kombu versions
Add Google Cloud Pub/Sub queues
Remove dependency fix
Fix json serialization of events for google pubsub

Add runworker command and some runworkers fixes

runworker command can be used to list all the workers, and run a single
worker, without multiprocessing and lifecycle management. Useful to let
the OS manage the worker, or run a single worker in a container.

Both commands now accept a --json arg to serialize the --list-workers
output in JSON. This can be used in setup scripts for example.

The --list-workers options of runworkers doesn't hang anymore if they
are no workers to launch.
Fix issue with pub/sub queues if no prometheus
Fix other issue with pub/sub queues if no prom
Fix GS_CREDENTIALS
Use default_storage for export tasks

New Google Santa enrollment

Simplified santa enrollment. Works with client certificates too. No need
to distribute a package anymore, just the generated configuration
profile.

WARNING: If you have currently enrolled santa agents, you need to
distribute the new configuration profile to re-enroll them.

Update santa configuration

Client TLS without issuer CN
Whitelist / Blacklist deprecation
BundlesEnabled deprecation
Remove release from enrollment form

commit_message: Add datadog event store
Fix kombu queues backend
Remove legacy saml2 docker-compose config

Better realms setup and error management.

Add test view for realm claims mapping.
Add error view when the callback (Zentral login for example) fails.
Require local superuser for realm managenemt.
Require non empty email and username for Zentral login.
Test uniqueness of email or username before allowing login.
Only set is_remote when user created from realm.
Allow tests on non login realms
Add default error pages
Add custom JSON logging formatters
Better attribute mapping in the datadog backend

Allow GET for realm login

The URL can be used for IdP initiated login now.

Allow IdP-initiated login for SAML realms

Use a default relay state for login

Better realms security

Save OpenID Connect state in user's session to avoid CSRF attacks
Do not allow IdP initiated logins for OpenID Connect
Verify InResponseTo in SAML response
Add setting to block IdP initiated logins for SAML
Add Jamf Protect contrib app
Add MetaMachine method to test recent snapshots
Add MachineSnapshots to jamf_protect
Fix realm test view
Update osquery releases tool
Add jamf extension attribute action
Fix google cloud pub sub dependency
Fix google cloud pub/sub preprocessor
add Humio event store

Munki scripts py3 upgrade

Use Munki's embedded python
Breaks compatibility which Munki < 5.1
Monolith new enrollment. Remove DEPNotify.
Remove duplicated certs from munki snapshot
Deduplicate and clean munki reported certs
Avoid 500 in machine views on ES errors
Refactor workers metrics. Add statsd exporter
Add transport options for kombu/celery
Add settings opts for AWS S3 storage
Add missing options for S3 django storage
Fix default https ES port

AWS SNS/SQS event queues backend

Introduce a new event queues backend for AWS, using SQS queues and SNS
topic / subscriptions.
Fix json serialization of events for aws sns sqs
Better config for monolith S3 repository backend
Slightly better monolith repo backends README
Fix bad sleeping strategy in sqs error handler
Add query language to kibana search URLs
Fix typo
Fix prometheus export in docker workers container
Better SAML error handling
Save expires_at in RAS. Pass RAS to callbacks.
Use NotOnOrAfter from SAML response
Fix next redirect on SSO logins
Fix SSO login session expiry
RAS in session. Use it for login/logout events.
Add realm session expiry configuration
Expiry in realm test mode. Add expiry for OIDC.
Block realms edit for local users using a realm
Catch extra pysaml2 errors
Remove old SAML env variables

Change configuration and container build

Introduce environment variable and file loading in base.json
configuration, with {{ env:XXX }} and {{ file:XXX }} patterns.

Use environment variables for configuration only in base.json.

Replace file based tls_server_certs and tls_server_key with
tls_fullchain and tls_privkey.

New Docker container multi-stage build.

Prepare docker entrypoint

Only use django db migration to wait for DB
Auto worker number for gunicorn

Load base.(json|ya?ml) from env first

Also, deprecate contact_groups. We need to find a better solution for
that.
Add runworker command to docker entrypoint
Do not trigger collectstatic with gunicorn cmd

Fix collectstatic run with ZENTRAL_CONF='{}'

Quick modifications to allow the django app to start without a propoer
zentral configuration. Used to prepare the static files.
Fix .dockerignore
Build tls_fullchain from cert & chain if missing

Add conf element proxy filter

To be able to extract a value from a list or a dict

Add B64GZIP_ZENTRAL_CONF for special cases

This loads the base.json from a b64 encoded compressed env var.

Fix 2 issues with the config objects

ConfigDict.copy() needs to return a ConfigDict to not break the proxied
values.
ConfigList.__iter__ needs to "render" the proxied values.

Add skip-if-existing option to create_zentral_user

Use it in the docker entrypoint to create the superuser and print the
invitation URL, if the superuser doesn't exist yet. Solves the issue
with the first access.

Fix gunicorn logging

Add missing gunicorn loggers to LOGGING configuration
Configure gunicorn access log format to avoid duplicated or irrelevant
information.

add django zentral settings LOG_ASCTIME boolean

LOG_ASCTIME toggles the timestamp in the console logs
Remove unused LOGGING filters

Add ZENTRAL_FORCE_ADMIN_PASSWORD_RESET

Forces the docker entrypoint to always print an password reset URL for
the admin user. Can be used to recover access if the first link was
missed or lost.

Fix the missing collected files manifest error

The static files need to be collected, even when serving them from a
different system, because the manifest is needed.

Introduce the api > fqdn / fqdn_mtls settings

We will start using them from now on, instead of tls_hostname_*.
Use PATH for celery in entrypoint

Add dev / aws / gcp app environment

 - split requirements.
 - default to "dev" env
 - "dev" env gets all dependencies and the tests/
 - add APP_ENV docker build arg
 - with DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1, only the necessary stages are built

Usage example:

```
DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1 docker build --build-arg APP_ENV=aws . -t zentral/zentral-aws
```
Fix default apps config bug
Do not try to create superuser during the tests

Set unusable password on user from realm

Django uses this as a signal to block the password resets.
Migrate tests from Travis CI to Github actions
Add bucket file, secret and param cfg proxies
Add robots meta tag with noindex, nofollow value

Fix probe sync bug when no probes

The sync thread would stop if there were no probes in the probe view,
because a probe view evaluates to False if empty. We now test if the
resolved weak reference is not None.

The liveness of the sync thread is also tested everytime the _load
method of a probe view is called, and a new thread is started if the
old one is dead – belt-and-suspenders.

Reboot the documentation

Use mkdocs and prepare push to read the docs
Import the deployment docs from the Wiki
Add dependency for read the docs
Use relative paths for docs images
Better docs logo and colors
Add monolith configuration

Update configuration

 - Remove `django.ADMINS` and `django.SERVER_EMAIL`. A better system needs
to be setup to catch the errors.
 - Build `api.fqdn` and `api.fqdn_mtls` from deprecated configuration
keys. Use them by default in `django.ALLOWED_HOSTED`.
Add configuration documentation
Add machine tags from jamf groups

Trigger tests on pull-requests

Add new svg based logo and remove old versions
Adjust dashboard colors and get closer to new logo

set color for documentation mobile view

Add basic inventory clients config test

Better solution for custom error pages

error pages that can be used by the HTTP proxy, when the application is
failing.
Remove buggy nginx error_page docker configurations. The new pages are
not configured, because they need to be built before they can be used.
It could be done in the docker-entrypoint, but the web app start is
already slow enough. PRs welcomed!
Use BuildKit
Add extra input checks for inventory extras
Test prettydescription escaping

Clean Jamf API client IP addresses

Apply the same normalization as the GenericIPAddressField with the
unpack_ipv4 option to avoid MTObject hash errors.
Add Jamf Webooks missing smart group permissions
Fix AWS SNS/SQS queues graceful shutdown

Disable RestAPIOperation Jamf webhook by default

The RestAPIOperation are triggered by Zentral own processing of some
events, amplifying the number of events to process!

Proceed carefully if you want to enable it!

First step.

Only update inventory on full inv events
Cache policies information (or absence of) for 5 min
Better logging in Jamf webhook preprocessor
Fix Jamf webhook event cleanup test

Clean munki enrollment if distributor

Remove existing pre/postflight setup during the enrollment, if the
package has a distributor, for example, if it is part of a Monolith
manifest.

Better monolith manifest catalogs forms

Fix typo in delete manifest catalog view
Add view to edit manifest catalogs tags
Avoid duplicated catalogs

Fixes #117

Better santa log parsing

Ignore rubbish data before timestamp
Fail hard when no timestamp found in event
Update santa log parsing tests

Monolith manifest N → 1 Meta business unit

Fixes #118
Fix duplicated grp warn. in Jamf API client
Remove duplicated apps in Jamf API client
Warning if Jamf raw event machine w/o SN
Avoid test collisions in test_users_views

add chrome principal user to machine snapshot

may not be the best implementation (original has open TODO's) but worth a shot to at least discuss
Fix some errors and add Google Chrome PU source
Add logged in user principal user via munki
Add serialize() method to BaseConfig
Fix munki job details view
Fix munki api tests
Add principal user search
Make serial number search field autofocus
Show principal user name in machine list
Flip test badge and docs urls to reflect 'main' branch
Change 'Edit on GitHub' URL to reflect main branch
Change master ref to main; rm extra whitespace

Add monolith manifest version

Also add timestamps
Preparation work for caching
Cache machine and tags in monolith munki views
Use monolith manifest pk and name for catalog
Remove meta_business_unit from MRBaseView
Use case for MRNameViews
Fix monolith cache server choice
Use http redirect for ppd if file URLs are secure
Block autocomplete on username search input
Add cache & remove old auth in munki API views
Send only one report during first postflight
Fix monolith mep and sma downlaod
Add deployment info in setup menu if available
Avoid error on users without NFSHomeDirectory
No redirect to unique manifest if no search terms
Cleanup runworker & add prometheus and statsd
Remove duplicated log run line
Add user info headers in nginx auth response

Swap localhostname with HostName

I don't see a reason to retain the previous behavior or an extra name to associate with the computer, nor was it straightforward to share from the ManagedInstallReport parsing happening elsewhere in postinstall, so using the same way munki gets it - comment explains fallback behavior (tested)
Use the os.uname result as a namedtuple
Add cloudfront option for monolith s3 repository
Use bundled munki python for monolith enrol. pkg.

Better inventory machine list views redirects

- Redirect to first page if out of page range
- Redirect to machine view if only one result and free input filters
(computer name, serial number, principal user name) used
Re-enable U2F for chrome

Fix osquery file carving transaction race

The background task to build the archive would start before the last
block was committed to the DB.
Use signed URL if possible for file carve archive

Add pincipal user to inventory export

Fixes #138

Accept updated content-encoding for santa

After a few years, santa (v1.17) is finally sending the correct
content-encoding header.

Add machine count to MacOS apps view

Also add ordering by bundle name and machine count.
Fix issue with MacOS apps table headers

Add monolith manifest sub manifests tagging view

Fixes #144
Add santa full_sync_interval and EnableSysxCache

Santa module major upgrade

Breaking changes!!! Santa probes will be migrated to Santa configuration
rules, and need to be checked.

commit_message:
Use faster DB query for apps search source field

The query that is exactly returning the current sources with apps in the
inventory is too slow. It needs to be optimized if possible. In the
meantime, we use the faster query to find all the inventory sources –
some of them without apps.

Add kibana_discover_url to ES configuration

The Kibana discovery endpoint path varies between Kibana versions.
Add last 6h time range to Kibana search URLs

Remove kibana_base_url from base.json examples

There are no kibana containers in the deployment examples.

Fix for santa preflight missing "client_mode" err

We have observed that the client_mode key is sometimes missing in the
data posted by santa on the preflight endpoint.
Deduplicate pkginfo in serialized manifest catalog
Increase Santa event detail URL field max length
Updated secretmanager to v1
Fix typo in conf GCP secret error message
Add pip constraints
Add missing dependency for GCP

Regroup accounts/ URLs

Move users admin and authentication views under the same path prefix.
This is cleaner and can help with an eventual request rate limiting
configuration.
Catch OverflowError in maybetimestamp

Fix NULL char error in realms login

A NULL char in the next URL could not be saved in the callback kwargs
attribute of the realm authentication session (NULL cannot be saved in a
jsonb postgres field).
The callback kwargs are sanitized now.

commit_message:
Fix munki postflight

Do not upload unfinished reports. This could happen if the postflight is
called during a Munki run, like when it is installed by monolith.
Add CHANGELOG.md
Add SECURITY.md
Update macOS build numbers
Update docker copy commands

AWS SNS/SQS queues update

Better logging
Multiple SNS send thread in EnrichWorker
Better event acknowledging in ConsumerProducer

Add ES bulk_store method

Also, avoid serializing and deserializing event. The machine metadata
should already be in the received serialized event.

Add AWS/SNS/SQS BatchConsumer

Use it with compatible stores

Better error handling in AWS SNS/SQS workers

Also: use exit status if available in the run_worker management command.

Refactor event stores

Do not paginate, but fetch more events
Serialize machine metadata in enrich worker
Add machine events url
Add elasticsearch machine events URL
Update Splunk event store
Support stores with only link to machine events
Add multiple store links to machine events view

Remove postgresql event store

It was never really good…
Fix event stores tests
Add Source & Service to datadog event filter
Remove legacy extra_probe_checks method

Add probes to event metadata at enrichment

The matching probes are added during the event enrichment. They are
serialized, and used during the event processing. They can be also
stored.
Avoid error when unknown probe event type

Refactor probe events

Use the serialized probe information to fetch the probe events
Replace pagination with "search after" continuation
Add time range and event type filters
Add links to event stores
Make probe dashboard and probe events optional
Probe events with datadog
Add Splunk probe events URL
Temporary fix the Osquery tests

Osquery contrib app overhaul

Migrate from Osquery custom probes to better suited dedicated Osquery
models for packs, scheduled queries, distributeds queries, …

**BREAKING CHANGE** legacy probe queries will be migrated, but please,
make sure you have backups before upgrading. You will have to manually
review and update the Osquery configurations after the upgrade, to
re-enable the scheduled queries. Older distributed query results will
not be deleted from the event stores, but you will not be able to fetch
them from the Zentral UI. Older file carving archives will not be

commit_message: Better run list in query detail page

Better widget to pick osquery platforms

Fixes #195
UI shortcuts to change query run valid until

Setup the group views. Rename the accounts URLs

It is necessary to rename the account URLs. User was implicit, and now
that there are groups, we have to rename the user views.

The views have been spit into different modules too.
Add realm group mappings

Add optional event namespace attribute

Some stores need to namespace the event payload to avoid attribute type
collisions. This is done by default using the event type as the
namespace. This introduce an optional "namespace" attribute that is set
to the event type by default.

Auth event overhaul & auto realm group mapping

* Update all the zentral authentication events
 * Use the same "zentral" namespace
 * Use consistent payload attributes
 * Move session information to metadata.request.user.session
 * Add MFA information to session
 * Separate create/delete verification device events
 * Add group membership events

* Update the remote user group memberships at login, based on the realm
group mappings and the realm user claims.
Exercice namespace attribute in the store tests
Add group user and realm mapping counts in list
Add macOS build 20D91

RBAC starts to work

It is used for the user and group management. It now needs to be wired
in the different Zentral apps.

* Consistent access to realm authentication info in session via proxy
object attached to the request.
* Refactoring of the menu system with link filtering by permissions and
locality of session
* Attach permissions to groups
* Fine grained permissions for user and group management
* User profile/settings views refactoring
* Possibility for a user to create and delete an API token
* Removed the possibility for an admin to create an API token for another
user. This is now only possible for service accounts
* Added group membership UI change events

commit_message: Fix osquery zentral API tests

Report munki full apps info & locally save tags

Add `apps_full_info_shard` for the munki app. This value if present is
sent to the postflight script, and will be use to decide if the full
application info (std + bundle display name and bundle version) will be
uploaded. If the option is absent, those info will not be uploaded. A
value between 1 and 100 will only activate this on some machines (%).

The job details API call has been moved to the preflight. The job
details are temporarily saved in the `/usr/local/zentral/munki` dir for
the postflight (to avoid a second API call). The preflight script looks
for the `tags` key in the job details and save them as `zentral_tags` in
the default `ConditionalItems.plist`. It is done in the preflight to
allow the tags to be used as soon as possible in during a munki run.

Munki pr/pstflght during inst. iff no distributor

Do not run pre/postflight scripts when installing from monolith for
example.

Delete existing job details from preflight

Better error reporting too

Write tags to /usr/local/zentral/munki/facts.plist

Do not use the temporary CondtionalItems.plist!!!

Add munki-facts module and standalone cond. script

These will make available the facts saved during the preflight

Add inventory_apps_shard to Jamf instance

To control the storage of the applications for the machines.
Default value: 100%.
Small optimization if inventory_apps_shard = 0
Add munki Configuration
Fixes #220
Add windows programs in inv via osquery
Add the program events and machine view
Use the new shard function
Fix munki enrollment distributor link
Disable DRF browsable renderer

Hide Action button when to perms.

See #221

Add proxied object to interact with the stores

Also add `events_url_authorized_groups` common store configuration key,
to set the list of group names whose members can be redirected to the
store. If not set, the events URLs will be displayed to all users. This
is used only if the store itself implements the requested events URLs.

The new Stores object has methods to filter the stores that implement
the requested events URLs and are authorized for a given user.
Use stores methods in machine and probe views
More robust host identifier detection

Add the missing DebianPackage fields

Filter the fields uploaded by osquery too…
Add tests of DebianPackage via osquery
Add the machine deb packages view back

Add exclude kwarg to MTObject serialize method

Exclude some fields from the output
Optimize MTObject diff if same objects
Test inventory_events_from_machine_snapshot_commit

Reorganize the machine update events

Replace the inventory update events with machine update events. Use the
same namespace "machine". This way, we maintain the same fields in the
events store accross the events. We also solve the "source" attribute
conflict. Finally, we separate the Add from the Remove event. This is to
facilitate the search in all the stores. This is possible now that we
are using a common namespace, without doubling the number of fields.

Fix timestamp parsing for splunk

Only a quickfix…
Fix machine events namespace
Add search in machine apps
Fix headers and row filter
Add machine apps, debs and programs exports

Build the ZIP locally and pass it to the storage

Avoid using the storage that can be remote as backend for the
ZipArchive. This fixes a bug seen with S3 storage.
Fix a potential file handle leak

Add API for machine mass-tagging

First implement a filter based on principal user unique id or principal
name.
Add group_name_set user attribute
Use groups in the extra links ctx proc.

RBAC on the nginx auth endpoint

Verify the first path element of the original URL received from Nginx
and compare it to the configured extra_links. If there is a match, and
the extra_link is configured with `authorized_groups` (list of group
names whose members are authorized to access the link), the access is
granted.
**WARNING**
If there is no match or there are no `authorized_groups` the access is
granted too!!! (Might change in the future, this is the legacy
behaviour.)
Fix extra links filtering in context processor

Fix RBAC nginx bug

An external link with RBAC was skipped if preceeded by another non-RBAC
link.
Test extra links context processor
Test nginx auth request with extra links
Remove nginx auth req unecessary check
Build custom 403 error page
Update .gitignore and .dockerignore
Fix slug conflicts in tag editing views
